{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/blog/2008-01-tradespotting-old-delhi_5577/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Chandni Chowk area of Old Delhi seems to be frozen in time, while the world around this island of civilisation has moved on. A visit to Chandni Chowk usually forms an essential milestone in the itinerary of a first time visitor to Delhi, especially if you're searching for the sights, sounds and smells of India as described in the guide books of an era gone by.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 629px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 101.840490797546%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"tradespotting1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0d5ac7cc3adb70c74967fe40c306765d/70d63/tradespotting1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0d5ac7cc3adb70c74967fe40c306765d/d2f63/tradespotting1.jpg 163w,\n/static/0d5ac7cc3adb70c74967fe40c306765d/c989d/tradespotting1.jpg 325w,\n/static/0d5ac7cc3adb70c74967fe40c306765d/70d63/tradespotting1.jpg 629w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 629px) 100vw, 629px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>On a few afternoons I went around 'Tradespotting Old Delhi' -- documenting the life of various businesses and the people behind the trades. Much of the work is done manually; from carrying heavy loads on shoulders to ferrying people across in rickshaws.</p>\n<style class=\"grvsc-styles\">\n  .grvsc-container {\n    overflow: auto;\n    position: relative;\n    -webkit-overflow